    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-03-01T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-03-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="1024"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1024">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 892.001/45.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Minister for Foreign Affairs of
                            Siam</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bangkok</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-03-01">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 1, 1911</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I received with thanks your excellency’s telegram announcing that the American
                    minister at Bangkok has been designated as special representative of the
                    President of the United States at the cremation of the remains of His Late
                    Majesty, King Chulalongkorn.</p>
                <p>I beg to say that His Majesty, my August Sovereign, is profoundly touched by the
                    courtesy thus shown and that the American minister will be favorably received in
                    the capacity your excellency desires.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Devawongse.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
